# UI Skills - Agent Configuration
# Add this section to your project's AGENTS.md or CLAUDE.md

## UI Skills Integration

UI Skills provide quality constraints for frontend development. These are behavioral guidelines that prevent common AI-generated interface issues.

### Available Skills

| Skill | Trigger | Purpose |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `/baseline-ui` | "apply constraints", "review UI", "check Tailwind" | Tailwind + motion constraints |
| `/frontend-design` | "design review", "anti-generic", "distinctive UI" | Anti-generic design guidance |
| `/ui-ux-pro-max` | "comprehensive UI", "professional interface" | Full UI/UX intelligence |
| `/next-best-practices` | "Next.js patterns", "App Router" | Next.js conventions |
| `/react-best-practices` | "React patterns", "component architecture" | React best practices |
| `/shadcn` | "shadcn/ui", "component workflow" | shadcn component patterns |
| `/make-interfaces-feel-better` | "polish UI", "micro-interactions" | Interface polish |
| `/interaction-design` | "microinteractions", "delightful UX" | Interaction patterns |
| `/swiss-design` | "grid discipline", "typography", "editorial" | Swiss design system |
| `/12-principles-of-animation` | "add animation", "motion design" | Animation principles |
| `/fixing-accessibility` | "a11y audit", "WCAG", "accessibility" | Accessibility compliance |

### Skill Selection Rules

**When starting a new UI feature:**
1. If using Tailwind → Load `baseline-ui`
2. If using Next.js → Load `next-best-practices`
3. If using React → Load `react-best-practices`
4. If design feels generic → Load `frontend-design`

**When reviewing existing UI:**
1. Load `baseline-ui <file>` to check constraints
2. Load `fixing-accessibility` for WCAG audit
3. Load `make-interfaces-feel-better` for polish pass

**When adding animations:**
1. Load `12-principles-of-animation` for motion quality
2. Load `interaction-design` for microinteractions

**When working on design systems:**
1. Load `swiss-design` for grid/typography discipline
2. Load `shadcn` for component workflow
3. Load `baseline-ui` for constraint enforcement

### Installation

```bash
# Install core skills
~/Documentos/ai/ui-skills/install.sh --default

# Install framework-specific
~/Documentos/ai/ui-skills/install.sh --framework-set

# Install all
~/Documentos/ai/ui-skills/install.sh --all
```

### Quality Gates

Before completing UI work:
1. Run `/baseline-ui <file>` to check constraints
2. Verify accessibility with `/fixing-accessibility`
3. Check motion quality (if animated) with `/12-principles-of-animation`

### Important Notes

- These skills are **constraints**, not creativity killers
- Not every rule applies to every situation - use judgment
- For trivial tasks, some rules can be relaxed
- When skills conflict, prioritize:
  1. Framework-specific skills (next-best-practices)
  2. Core quality (baseline-ui)
  3. Design guidance (frontend-design)
